<p>Alice Holden is fast becoming a role model for young farmers. She is one of a small group, but a growing one, of young people who are choosing a career on the land. She has worked on many farms and has fallen in love with each and every one of them. The farms have given her insights and perhaps even challenge our notions of what it means to be a farmer and our image of farms themselves.</p>
<p>Having had her hands in the earth for almost a decade she has learned about the soil, agriculture, scale, and&nbsp;ownership.</p>